We use the nbastatR library to extract data from the NBA. Were primarily concerned with finding causal effects in the data where some instance of random assignment, exogeneity, or matching can be assumed to better model counterfactuals.

Clustering players

player_stats <- players %>%
  filter(minutesTotals > 1500) %>%
  select(namePlayer, starts_with("ratio")) %>% #, starts_with("pct")) %>%
  mutate_if(is.numeric, scale) %>%
  column_to_rownames("namePlayer")
methods <- c("ward.D", "ward.D2", "single", "complete", "average", "mcquitty",
             "median", "centroid")
sapply(methods, FUN=function(method) {
  plot(hclust(dist(as.matrix(player_stats)), method = method))
})
